Abe Pollin, a prominent figure in professional sports, has passed away. President Obama expressed his sadness at the news and praised Pollin for his contributions to the world of sports. Pollin believed that being an owner meant more than just winning championships; it was about helping young athletes grow as individuals and being a part of the community. He invested his own fortune into revitalizing Washington, D.C., a city he loved. The President noted that Pollin was committed to the teams he guided, generous to those in need, and loyal to the people of D.C. The President offered his condolences to Pollin's family.